  "local_port": 48252,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some mind-blowing Pc tools that exist that most people don't know about?",
  "response": "There are many powerful and niche PC tools that can significantly enhance productivity, creativity, or efficiency, yet remain relatively unknown to the average user. Here are some mind-blowing tools that deserve more attention:\n\n---\n\n### **Productivity & Automation**\n1. **AutoHotkey (AHK)**  \n   A scripting language that allows you to automate repetitive tasks, create custom keyboard shortcuts, and remap keys. It\u2019s incredibly powerful for streamlining workflows.  \n   **Example**: Automate form-filling or create a one-click button to open your favorite apps.\n\n2. **Flux**  \n   Adjusts your screen\u2019s color temperature based on the time of day to reduce eye strain and improve sleep quality. It\u2019s a simple yet effective tool for long hours at the computer.\n\n3. **Notion**  \n   An all-in-one workspace for notes, databases, task management, and collaboration. It\u2019s highly customizable and can replace multiple apps like Trello, Evernote, and Google Docs.\n\n4. **Ditto Clipboard Manager**  \n   A clipboard history tool that saves everything you copy, allowing you to paste items from your history. It\u2019s a game-changer for anyone who frequently copies and pastes.\n\n---\n\n### **File Management & Search**\n5. **Everything by Voidtools**  \n   A lightning-fast file search tool for Windows. It indexes your files and allows you to search them instantly, unlike the built-in Windows search.\n\n6. **WizTree**  \n   Analyzes your hard drive and shows which files and folders are taking up the most space. It\u2019s much faster than Windows Disk Cleanup.\n\n7. **FreeFileSync**  \n   A file synchronization tool that helps you back up and sync files between folders or drives. It\u2019s simple, reliable, and highly customizable.\n\n---\n\n### **Creative & Multimedia**\n8. **OBS Studio**  \n   A free and open-source tool for video recording and live streaming. It\u2019s widely used by content creators but is also great for recording presentations or tutorials.\n\n9. **HandBrake**  \n   A video transcoder that converts video files into different formats. It\u2019s lightweight, open-source, and supports a wide range of codecs.\n\n10. **Voicemeeter**  \n    A virtual audio mixer that lets you manage and route audio from different sources. It\u2019s perfect for streamers, podcasters, or anyone who needs advanced audio control.\n\n---\n\n### **System Optimization**\n11. **Process Hacker**  \n    A more advanced alternative to Task Manager. It provides detailed information about running processes, services, and network activity, with the ability to manipulate them.\n\n12. **CCleaner**  \n    A system optimization tool that cleans up junk files, fixes registry issues, and manages startup programs. It\u2019s great for keeping your system running smoothly.\n\n13. **Malwarebytes AdwCleaner**  \n    A lightweight tool specifically designed to remove adware and unwanted programs that often slip past traditional antivirus software.\n\n---\n\n### **Networking & Security**\n14. **Wireshark**  \n    A network protocol analyzer that captures and displays data traveling over your network in real-time. It\u2019s invaluable for troubleshooting network issues or learning about network traffic.\n\n15. **KeePass**  \n    A password manager that stores your passwords in an encrypted database. It\u2019s offline, open-source, and highly secure.\n\n16. **Hedges**  \n    A tool for securely erasing files and ensuring they cannot be recovered. It\u2019s useful for permanently deleting sensitive data.\n\n---\n\n### **Utilities & Fun Tools**\n17. **Greenshot**  \n    A lightweight screenshot tool with annotation features. It\u2019s faster and more versatile than the default snipping tool.\n\n18. **WinDirStat**  \n    Visualizes your disk usage with a color-coded map, making it easy to identify which files or folders are consuming the most space.\n\n19. **Rainmeter**  \n    A desktop customization tool that lets you add widgets, skins, and live data (like weather, system stats, or calendars) to your desktop.\n\n20. **Synergy**  \n    Allows you to control multiple computers with one keyboard and mouse. It\u2019s perfect for multi-device setups.\n\n---\n\n### **Developer Tools**\n21. **Postman**  \n    A tool for testing and documenting APIs. It\u2019s essential for developers but can also be useful for anyone working with web services.\n\n22. **Visual Studio Code (VS Code)**  \n    A lightweight yet powerful code editor with tons of extensions for almost any programming language or workflow.\n\n23. **GitHub Desktop**  \n    Simplifies Git version control for those who prefer a graphical interface over command-line Git.\n\n---\n\nThese tools can save time, enhance productivity, or unlock new possibilities for your PC usage. Depending on your needs, you might find some of them indispensable!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
